# Phase 5 — Task Extraction Agent

## Overview
Reads Gmail every hour, uses Groq AI to identify real action items, and automatically creates tasks in Notion. Skips promotional, junk, and automated emails.

## Workflow
Schedule Trigger (every hour) → Get Many Messages (Gmail) → HTTP Request (Groq AI) → If Node (filter NO_TASKS) → Create Database Page (Notion) → Add Label (Gmail) → Mark as Read (Gmail)

## Nodes

### 1. Schedule Trigger
- Runs every 1 hour

### 2. Get Many Messages (Gmail)
- Fetches up to 10 unread emails
- Excludes emails labelled AI-Processed

### 3. HTTP Request (Groq AI)
- Model: llama-3.3-70b-versatile
- Extracts: Task, Priority, Description, From
- Returns NO_TASKS for promotional/junk emails

### 4. If Node
- Filters out NO_TASKS responses
- Only passes real tasks to Notion

### 5. Create Database Page (Notion)
- Database: AI Tasks
- Fields: Task, Priority, Description, Source (Email), Status (To Do)

### 6. Add Label (Gmail)
- Adds AI-Processed label to processed emails

### 7. Mark as Read (Gmail)
- Marks processed emails as read to prevent reprocessing

## Credentials Needed
- Gmail OAuth
- Groq API Key
- Notion API Key

